
The standard library {\tt Threadkit\_Pure\_Io} api defines access to ``pure'' (side-effect free) input for multithreaded Mythryl programs. 
(No attempt is made to implement pure output.)

Implementations of {\tt Pure\_Io} may be generated using  
{\tt binary\_io\_g} and {\tt text\_io\_g} from respectively 
\ahrefloc{src/lib/std/src/io/binary-io-g.pkg}{src/lib/std/src/io/binary-io-g.pkg} and 
\ahrefloc{src/lib/std/src/io/file-g.pkg}{src/lib/std/src/io/file-g.pkg}.

Predefined packages generated by those two include the standard library \ahrefloc{pkg:file}{file} and 
\ahrefloc{pkg:binary\_io}{binary\_io} packages.

The {\tt Pure\_Io} api source code is in \ahrefloc{src/lib/std/src/io/pure-io.api}{src/lib/std/src/io/pure-io.api}.

See also: \ahrefloc{api:Threadkit\_Pure\_Io}{Threadkit\_Pure\_Io}.

See also: \ahrefloc{pkg:pure\_io}{pure\_io}.

See also: \ahrefloc{api:Imperative\_Io}{Imperative\_Io}.
